Colouration. Labrum pale brown, usually with slightly darkened middle part. Elytra with small humeral spots and large discal spot with anterior margin oblique and reaching apex of scutellum, lateral margin straight and parallel with elytral margin, posterior margin transverse, slightly uneven (
Fig. 35, 36
). In some females anterior margin of large discal spot transversely straight in middle (
Fig. 37
).

Head (
Fig. 16
) with large frontal impression covered with large punctures and horizontal wrinkles. Anterior clypeal processes narrow, with inner margins parallel, outer margins oblique and with apical tips rounded, clypeal margin between processes pointed in middle. Mandibles relatively narrow, with sharp dorsal keel. Only inner slopes of mandibles visible in dorsal view.

Aedeagus (
Fig. 4
). Dorsal impression large, subtriangular with widely rounded apex, often with two additional small impressions basally. Apical quarter of aedeagus subtriangular with slightly concave sides, tip shortly rounded. Operculum subpentagonal. Apex of aedeagus without inward triangular crooked folds. Visible part of anterior sclerite forming thin trident star. Ventral side with two elongate impressions subapically.

Everted aedeagus (
Fig. 22
). Ejaculatory guide with flat ventral side, lateral sides flat, subtriangular, rightangled to ventral side, middle part with long slightly round process directed backwards. Lateral sclerites small, triangular. Anterior sclerite small, forming two concave plates connected in basal suture.

Spermatheca (
Fig. 10
). Vasculum widely round, apical part with round apex, basal part distinctly wider. Bulbus small, subtriangular. Ductus spermathecae very long, ca 6 times as long as vasculum, proximally nearly straight, distally with simple loops.
